The paper deals with the construction of designs from codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The use of designs in coding theory also makes it relevant to the sub-category of coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the properties of the codes used, which may be of interest to the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the construction of designs involves solving systems of equations, which falls under the sub-category of numerical analysis (cs.NA).
